article.headline: Vermont 63, Iona 50
article.story: BURLINGTON, Vt. (AP) -- Colin McIntosh scored 14 points and Kyle Cieplicki and Mike Trimboli each added 10 in Vermont's 63-50 victory over the winless Iona Sunday. Vermont (5-4) took a 37-30 lead at halftime after McIntosh scored 12 in the first half on 5-of-5 shooting. The Catamounts led by double digits for much of the second half. Chris Holm grabbed 15 rebounds and scored seven points for the Catamounts. Justin Marshall came off the bench to score 15 points for Iona (0-7), while Anthony Bruin added 13. Iona was held to 31.6 percent shooting for the game.
